  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will investigate the changes in the reflux symptom index (RSI) and reflux finding
      score (RFS) among patients with obstructive sleep apnea after regular humidified CPAP
      therapy. Since these two diseases have strong associations then one may consider the possible
      benefits from therapy in between them.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
